Subject: Mechanical Consultant Proposal Request - 58 Lawrence St, Peakhurst
Dear Felix,
Thanks for your time yesterday.
As discussed, you've come recommended by Jad and we're hoping to close out
the consultant list this week, so not leaving you much time to quote.
we would like to invite you to submit a fee proposal for Mechanical
consultancy services for construction documentation and declaration under
the DBPA for the following:
*	Site Address: 58 Lawrence Street, Peakhurst NSW 2210
*	Site Area: 594.4m2
*	Neighbouring properties: Predominantly 1-2 storey dwellings
*	The proposal includes the following:
*	Demolition of existing Single dwelling
*	Construction of 4 storey boarding house w/ basement car park 
*	20 total Studio units
*	1 level of basement car parking with 10 car spaces (1 accessible),
accessed via Lawrence Street
Scope of Works should include but not be limited to the following:
*	Preparation of Mechanical plans and specification in accordance with
Georges River Council Development Consent for Development Application No.
DA2019/0626
Proposal should also outline the following:
*	Timeframe - 
*	Early Works CC: 12 Weeks
*	DCD: 16 Weeks
*	Client would ideally like to be onsite: 1 July 2024 
*	Payment Terms - Client preference is for 
*	50% of total fee on engagement
*	50% of total fee on completion
*	Hourly rates for additional services post submission
To assist in the preparation of the proposal please find a dropbox link to
the following documents:
*	Stamped Plans
*	Development Consent

Email sent from Rachid Andary on May 1, 2024, with architecture drawings.
The project is a residential develop and consists of:
-      1 level of Basement car park, approximately 10 car spots.
-      Building ground to level 3, with boarding rooms, approximately 20 ensuites.

Installation Reference.Program:
Week 1: site induction, site inspection and site measure, coordination.
Week 2-3: Order ductwork, VCDs, material and arrange labour.
Week 4-5: Installation commissioning and testing to critical area.
Week 6-8: Based on site condition, finalize all installation, provide installation certificate.

Extent.Item: Review of all drawings relevant to the car park design.
Creation of a three-dimensional model for the car park suitable for the CFD simulations.
CFD ventilation simulations to assess the performance of the proposed design. This will provide a basis on which to compare subsequent designs.
CFD ventilation simulations for up to three design changes. This includes altering natural ventilation openings, supply/exhaust flow rates, re-locating jet fans, etc.
Preparation of a Technical Report detailing the results and recommendations.

Clarifications.Item: We have allowed 3 off model simulation/modification, if additional simulations are required (for example, in the event of still unacceptable CO levels) then these will be discussed with the client and will be subject to a variation.
We have not allowed fire engineering solution for jet fan which might affect sprinkler performance, this will need to be addressed by fire engineer on the job.
